<body>
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <h1>Dhanu Yatra</h1>
            <p>The World’s Largest Open-Air Theater</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="contain">
        <div class="main-content">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Historical Significance</h2>
                <p>
                    Dhanu Yatra, held in Bargarh, reenacts Krishna’s visit to Mathura and the defeat of King Kansa. Dating
                    back to the 1940s, it began as a post-independence cultural expression. Spanning 11 days, this grand
                    theater transforms the town into a living stage, rooted in mythology and Odisha’s artistic heritage.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Cultural Highlights</h2>
                <p>
                    The festival turns Bargarh into Mathura and nearby Ambapali into Gopapura, with locals and actors
                    performing in streets and fields. Kansa’s royal processions, folk dances, and Odissi music bring the
                    epic to life. It’s a mesmerizing blend of devotion, drama, and community spirit, unparalleled in scale.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Food and Cuisine</h2>
                <p>
                    During Dhanu Yatra, stalls serve Odia favorites like Pakhala Bhata, Chhena Poda, and pithas (rice cakes).
                    Visitors enjoy spicy snacks, jaggery sweets, and refreshing drinks like Bela Pana. The food complements
                    the festive vibe, offering a taste of Odisha’s rustic culinary traditions.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Shopping Experience</h2>
                <p>
                    Temporary markets spring up, selling handicrafts, Sambalpuri textiles, and souvenirs tied to the festival.
                    Visitors can buy wooden props, clay idols, and traditional jewelry. It’s a vibrant bazaar where local
                    artisans showcase their skills, adding to the cultural immersion.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Festive Atmosphere</h2>
                <p>
                    Dhanu Yatra transforms Bargarh into a theatrical wonderland. Kansa’s mock rule—complete with elephants
                    and decrees—fills the air with excitement. Thousands gather to watch the drama unfold across 15 km,
                    blending mythology with reality in a spectacle of color, sound, and celebration.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar">
            <h2>Event Details</h2>
            <div class="details-grid">
                <div class="detail-item">
                    <strong>Location:</strong> <span>Bargarh, Odisha</span>
                </div>
                <div class="detail-item">
                    <strong>Timing:</strong> <span>December-January (post-Dhanu Sankranti)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="detail-item">
                    <strong>Duration:</strong> <span>11 Days</span>
                </div>
                <div class="detail-item">
                    <strong>Entry:</strong> <span>Free</span>
                </div>
            </div>
